snippet.textDisplay:
Nice composition and Sukhwinder at his best. But why can't Indian Coke Studio present the original classics? They need to respect the classics and present them as is instead of morphing the classics into some kind of weird remix. The lyrics of this song was shamelessly copied from Punjabi folk songs. Here are some examples:
1) Punjabi wedding song "Veer vyahvan chaliya ..." has been deformed as "Peer manavan chaliya ..."
2) Punjabi ballad called "Vaar" has been bastardized from "Mere desh de banke gabru - Pagga rang birangiyan" with ode to the brave hearts of Punjab and their colorful turbans to "Bhasha rang birangiyan ..." meaning the colorful languages of India.
